[div class=p 
	"So, this is my first submission here, and since I am pretty new to tool assisted running, I decided to go with a game I wasted my last two years on: Tetris.
	$LF
	"I decided to get the NES rom and FCEUX and started toying around, then I made this "secret grade" run.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The goal is basically to build to the top of the field leaving one hole per line, starting bottom left and up to the right, then keep building up in the other direction, leaving holes in a ">" shape. The reason this is called secret grade is because it is an actual thing to do in the Tetris: the Grand Master series, and when you do it, you get rewarded with a "secret grade" at the end of your game.
	$LF
	"I then decided to restrict the piece drops to only O, I and T, just to have the entire field filled with white blocks, making the result better for the eyes. I didn't go with S/J or Z/L because it would have made the challenge way too hard, if not impossible.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Then it was all about re-recording almost every piece drop to get a good piece on the "NEXT" box.
	$LF
]div
